data.title: Martijn de Zwart
data.text:
Dutch footballer

Martijn de Zwart (Dutch pronunciation: [mɑrˈtɛi̯n də ˈsʋɑrt]; born 8 November 1990) is a Dutch footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Dutch Tweede Divisie club Quick Boys, where he is also the current goalkeeping coach.

Career

[edit]

A prospect of Quick Boys, De Zwart moved to ADO Den Haag in July 2011.[1] At ADO, he was mostly a backup for Gino Coutinho and Robert Zwinkels, but he managed to make his professional debut on 9 March 2013 in a 1–1 draw in the Eredivisie match against AZ.[2] In June 2013, he signed a one-year contract extension with the club.[3]

After the expiration of his contract on 30 June 2014, De Zwart returned to childhood club Quick Boys.[4]

After six years at Quick Boys, where he mainly played as a backup in the later years, De Zwart became goalkeepers coach in July 2020, while continuing as a backup to starter Paul van der Helm.[5]

Honours

[edit]

Quick Boys

Hoofdklasse: 2015–16[6]

Individual

Quick Boys Player of the Season: 2009–10[7]
